recent_25_results.question: 4.1 What are the two different ways of specifying the length of an array?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.1 Initializing the size in the brackets: int a[100]; Initializing the length by assigning variables: int a[] = {1,2,3};

recent_25_results.question: 4.1 What are the two different ways of specifying the length of an array?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.1 user defined value or by the number of elements in initializer list

recent_25_results.question: 4.1 What are the two different ways of specifying the length of an array?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.1 you can assign the size of it inside the brackets when you declare the array [3], or you can have it set by how many items you set the array equal to {1,2,3}

recent_25_results.question: 4.1 What are the two different ways of specifying the length of an array?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.1 use an arraylist, or have your program ask the array how many elements it has. As an obj it it should have member length that is the number of slots it has.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 strings that are used in an char array are much easier to manipulate than as a string object, because each character is stored separately rather than as a whole

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 the type string uses less storage and you have to change the string all at once. with an array of characters you can make permutations of words using the characters stored in the array, without needing to actually access and change the variables. with an array of characters you can just change how they're accessed.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 Unlike in a string declared using type string, in a string declared using an array of characters the programmer must provide the null terminating character and must ensure the array is large enough to hold the string and null terminating character.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 All strings represented by character arrays end with the null character. You declare an object of type string just like any other type, for example: string s;

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 By using an array of characters, one can store and manipulate the strings rather than just having a type string variable.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 type string is an array of chars that will make an array of single letter characters while an array of strings will be an actual array of words (or an array of char arrays)

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 They're basically the same, however, a string ends w/ a null character, denoting the end of the string (and the size). A char array has potential to be any size, so it must be declared or limited.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 string is a class in the standard library and has method that modify it. Whereas the char array is on able to be modifie by the user.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 By using an array of characters, you are limited to the size of the array of characters. By declaring by type the end of the string is acknowledged by white space.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 The data class type string are designed to handle character data, and has many functions built into the class library to deal with them. An array of characters however is subject to all the same rules of any other array with no real additional functionality. Another difference is that the string class deals with the null character implicitly, unlike an array of characters, which must handle the null character explicitly.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 string declared used in an array of characters contains each character in the array and a special string-termination character called the null character versus the type string.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 A char array reads a string as each individual character. A string literal array reads the entire string.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 array of characters can only hold as many characters as the array size and strings are not that limited.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 Stings can only be modified by functions of the String class, an array of characters can be modified by the user

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 if by type string, the array contains an additional terminating null character

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 The array of characters has a null character \0 at the end of the array to signify the array's end. The string does not have this.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 strings with type string are just that. Strings. They are not part of an array list at all where as one declared by an array is actually an array of characters able to be pointed and detected.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 the array of characters has a set length, while the type string has virtually unlimited length.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 Char array - Individual letters can be accessed directly with array subscript notation. String array - array subscript will return the entire string.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 array of characters need a termination character as well as size specification whether its explicit or implicit.

recent_25_results.question: 4.2 What is the main difference between strings declared using the type string versus strings declared using an array of characters?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 4.2 when using an array individual characters can be accessed and manipulated.
